ve simmering basket with aid of spatula and rinse rice until water runs clear. Transfer rice into a seperate bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place water, stock paste, ginger, soy sauce and sesame oil into mixing bowl. Insert simmering basket. Place chicken into it and poach <b>10 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>."},{"content":"Stir chicken with spatula to ensure even cooking and cook <b>5-7 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b> or until chicken is just cooked. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula and transfer chicken into a thermal serving bowl or other large bowl. Pour half of the stock over the chicken. Cover to keep warm."},{"content":"If required, top up remaining stock level in mixing bowl with extra water until it reaches 1L mark."},{"content":"Insert simmering basket back into mixing bowl. Add rinsed rice and cook <b>10-13 min\/100°C\/speed 4<b> or until cooked."},{"content":"Place mounds of rice into 4 serving bowls. Cut chicken into bite-size pieces and divide between bowls. Drizzle 1-2 tablespoons of the stock over chicken. Garnish with spring onions\/shallots, mint, cucumber and serve with reserved Nuoc cham dressing on the side."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook <\/em>or <em>Everyday Cookbook <\/em>for the Chicken stock paste recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h","4 portions"]}